---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="With Agents — Practical coding-agent workflows"
  description="A source-backed field guide to coding-agent workflows: durable context, alignment, proof, small threads, Amp, generated slides, and curated resources."
  canonicalPath="/"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-24">
    <section class="space-y-8">
      <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-indigo-600">
        Practical coding-agent workflows
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-light leading-tight text-gray-950">
          A practical field guide for agentic coding in 2026.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-600 font-light leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          With Agents is a source-backed series about coding agents: durable repo-local context, the current landscape, risk-scaled evidence, small-thread operating practice, an Amp case study, and the resource library that grounds the writing.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
        <a href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-gray-900 px-5 py-3 text-white transition-colors duration-200 hover:bg-gray-700 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          Start with durable context
        </a>
        <a href="/resources/coding-with-agents" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-lg border border-gray-300 px-5 py-3 text-gray-800 transition-colors duration-200 hover:border-gray-400 hover:bg-gray-50 focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          Browse resources
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-6">
      <div class="space-y-3">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-600">
          Core entry points
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-light text-gray-900">
          Start by the problem you need to solve.
        </h2>
        <p class="max-w-3xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
          These are the current entry points for using coding agents deliberately: keep context durable, scale proof to risk, preserve useful handoffs, and trace claims back to source material.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <a href="/posts/durable-context-coding-agents" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Context anchor</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Your Repo Is the Memory</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A field guide for keeping coding agents aligned with repo-local truth, shared state, proof, and human judgment.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/posts/agentic-coding-2026" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Series map</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Agentic Coding in 2026</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A practical field guide to cheap implementation, alignment, proof, useful friction, codebase infrastructure, context hygiene, and factory-era workflows.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/posts/make-the-agent-prove-it" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Proof stack</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Make the Agent Prove It</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A risk-scaled ladder for tests, real-system checks, conformance suites, evidence artifacts, sandboxing, and review.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/posts/small-threads-durable-state" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Workflow practice</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Small Threads, Durable State</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A day-to-day procedure for wide research, narrow implementation, work items, handoffs, progress logs, and verification records.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/posts/amp-factory-era-case-study" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Tool case study</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Amp as a Factory-Era Case Study</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">A current Amp example for task sizing, delegation contracts, context hygiene, proof loops, review, and orchestration.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/resources/coding-with-agents" class="rounded-xl border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 transition-all duration-200 hover:border-gray-300 hover:shadow-lg focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-indigo-600/50 focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-600">Source trail</p>
          <h3 class="mb-3 text-2xl font-light text-gray-900">Curated talks and summaries</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Podcasts, videos, articles, and transcript-backed notes you can scan before watching.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="rounded-2xl bg-slate-50 p-8 md:p-10">
      <div class="space-y-3 mb-8">
        <p class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-indigo-600">
          How to use this site
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-light text-gray-900">
          Treat the site as a workflow map, not just an archive.
        </h2>
        <p class="max-w-3xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          The public pages are designed for different moments: learning a pattern, sharing it with a team, checking the evidence behind a claim, or finding the full index.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-5 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Read a guide for an operating pattern</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Use the field guides when you need a practical model for context, proof, delegation, handoffs, or review.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Open slides when you need to brief people</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            Each post header includes a “View as slides” link, so the same source-backed writing can become a talk outline or team review.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Trace claims through the resource library</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            The resources page collects talks, videos, articles, and transcript-backed summaries that ground the writing.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-slate-200 bg-white/70 p-5">
          <h3 class="mb-2 text-lg font-medium text-gray-900">Use the archive when you want everything</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            The homepage stays curated. The <a class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500" href="/posts">posts archive</a> carries the listed writing, and the <a class="text-indigo-700 hover:text-indigo-500" href="/resources">resources index</a> points to the maintained resource collections.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
